result.execSummary:
The defendant Amber Marie Larsin was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Amber Marie Larsin is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Amber Marie Larsin was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 10:25 a.m. Court notes this matter is set for a pre trial conference.  ADA Ellenwood states there is a resolution. Recites agreement. Victim's Rights have been complied with.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads NO CONTEST to Ct 2 Misd. Battery in 16CF42. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 2 Misd. Battery in 16CF42. On motion of the State without objecton, Crt dismisses Ct's 1 & 3 in 16CF42. Sentencing arguments. 20 days to file appeal. 

Crt orders: 

-   S/W 1 year probation. To run concurrent to Polk Co. probation sentence in 15CF389

-   41 days presentence credit if probation is revoked

-  Court costs of $243.00

-  DNA Sample and $200.00 Surcharge

-   Complete all other programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the Department of Corrections

-   AODA and follow any recommended treatment.

-     It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Amanda Catlin.
